(442, 1, '2014-07-07 11:42:26', '2014-07-07 01:42:26', 'Which Visa?\r\n\r\nFor your convenience, we have listed some of the most common visa solutions on this site.\r\n\r\nAs this is an overview only we recommend clarifying which visa solution suits your individual circumstances and matches your immigration goal best. To do this, contact us or try our Free Online Visa Assessment so that we can give you individual advice on the most suitable visa type for you and your personal circumstances\r\n\r\nWe regularly release the latest news about granted Australian visas, success stories and the present Australian job market on our news site.', 'Visa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'visa', '', '', '2014-07-20 02:44:20', '2014-07-19 16:44:20', '', 409, 'http://localhost/southpac/?page_id=442', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(445, 1, '2014-07-07 11:52:54', '2014-07-07 01:52:54', 'Australia has a long history of welcoming migrants and visitors from all over the world. Some come temporarily as tourists or to visit relatives and friends, some take advantage of Australias excellent high schools and universities while others come as employees or to start a business. Many people who come to Australia temporarily decide they want to remain permanently.\r\n\r\nRegardless of your reason, if you would like to come to Australia either temporarily or permanently, short stay or long stay, Australia Asian Sunlight Company (AASUNCO) offers a full range of Australian visa and migration services.  Our registered migration agents will draw on their many years of Australian immigration expertise to professionally advise you on your options.\r\n\r\nAustralian immigration law is complex and constantly changing, there are over one hundred types of visas you can apply for. Applying for the wrong visa can be costly. We can guide you through the entire process, from choosing the right visa to suit your individual circumstances and preparing your application right through to the final interview and obtaining your visa.\r\n\r\nYou are welcome to contact us with any questions you may have. Whether your goal is simply to study or travel in Australia for a short time or for your family to live permanently in Australia, we can assist you in achieving your objective.\r\n\r\nUnder Australian law anybody offering migration advice must be registered with the government. Only persons who pass the strict requirements of the Migration Agents Registration Authority (MARA) are allowed to be registered. We are members of the Migration Institute of Australia and all our advisers are registered migration agents bound to abide by MARAs Code of Conduct.', 'Immigration', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'immigration', '', '', '2014-07-20 02:55:07', '2014-07-19 16:55:07', '', 409, 'http://localhost/southpac/?page_id=445', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(447, 1, '2014-07-07 11:53:11', '2014-07-07 01:53:11', '<div class="grid_5">\r\n[youtube url="http://youtu.be/WODEoepR4sU"]\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nSouthpac Services currently have established partnership with many Australian Colleges, Universities and TAFFs. Contact us now for a School Application, our professional consultant will make best study plan for your future stay in Australia.\r\n\r\n', 'Student', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'student', '', '', '2014-07-20 02:43:08', '2014-07-19 16:43:08', '', 409, 'http://localhost/southpac/?page_id=447', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(451, 1, '2014-07-07 11:54:19', '2014-07-07 01:54:19', 'The Migration Review Tribunal (MRT) and Refugee Review Tribunal (RRT) conduct merit reviews of visa and visa-related decisions made by the Australian Department of Immigration and Border Protection.\r\n\r\nMerits review is an administrative reconsideration of a case. A merits review body makes decisions within the same legislative framework as the primary decision maker, and may exercise all the powers and discretions conferred on the primary decision maker.\r\n\r\nMRT: Reviews a wide range of decisions in relation to visas other than protection visas\r\nRRT: Reviews decisions in relation to protection visas.\r\nThe tribunals are usually constituted by a single member. The tribunals have the power to affirm the primary decision, vary the primary decision, set aside the primary decision and substitute a new decision, or remit (return) a matter to the department for reconsideration with specific directions.\r\n\r\nIn reviewing a decision to refuse or cancel a visa, the tribunals are required to conduct a merits review that is independent, fair, just, economical, informal and quick. We aim to make the correct decision in individual cases, and to influence decision-making through quality and consistency of our decisions.', 'Tribunal', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tribunal', '', '', '2014-07-20 03:09:35', '2014-07-19 17:09:35', '', 409, 'http://localhost/southpac/?page_id=451', 0, 'page', '', 0),
